Use the standard library
This is how to is_nested of string:
  Remember that depth is 0
  Remember that seen_open is 0
  Do this string's length times:
    Remember that ch is item depth in string
    When ch is 91, then:
      Increase depth
      Remember that seen_open is 1
    End when
    When ch is 93, then:
      Decrease depth
      When depth is less than 0, then:
        The answer is 0
      End when
    End when
  End do
  When seen_open is 1, then:
    When depth is 0, then:
      The answer is 1
    End when
  End when
  The answer is 0
Now you know